main event: An unknown object exploded in the sky, with a further explosion on the surface of the water at 17.53N 57-40W near San Juan, Puerto Rico.
interesting points: The object was observed by the crew of the SS Plainsman ship.
The report was transmitted to the U.S. Coast Guard in San Juan, Puerto Rico.
The incident occurred at 2149Z on March 19, 1963.
The U.S. Coast Guard was searching the area for more information.
The report was further distributed to various military and intelligence agencies, including the Air Force, Navy, and Defense Intelligence Agency.
witnesses: crew of the SS Plainsman ship
